    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Repeating/paraphrasing here since the logs aren't available for context:\n\nMy main objection is that this goes against our long-standing rule that Lua APIs should be task oriented and not directly bridge trait properties.  This is especially true for the weather trait because (a) its properties are low level and a bit horrible, and (b) we already know that these need to change (extracting wind out so that it can also affect gas particles in TS), and baking the current trait setup into our nominally-stable Lua API makes that much harder.\n"
  },
